# Project Structure

Standard folder layouts for every project type. Adapt to the framework - the logical grouping should be consistent, but framework conventions (Remix loaders, Nest modules, Rails engines) take precedence over this template.

> Folder names and example files below are `[DEFAULT]` illustrations - adapt to your project's domain and framework. Feature-grouping is preferred when features are self-contained; type-grouping (routes/, controllers/, services/) is acceptable when the framework or team convention calls for it. Be consistent within each project.

---

## The Golden Rule

**A stranger should open the project and instantly know where everything lives.** If someone has to search for "where do API routes go?" - the structure has failed.

---

## Placement tests (every web app)

### URL mirror test

Route folders follow **URL segments**: `/login` -> route folder `login/`; `/auth/settings` -> under `auth/`. Do not pile unrelated screens at the app root.

### Colocation test

Feature-specific UI lives **beside its route** (framework colocation: `_components/`, route-local `components/`, or equivalent) - not domain screen modules at a shared `components/` root.

### Shared components root

At `components/` (or equivalent) top level, allow only **shared** areas:

- `ui/` - primitives (`Button`, `DataTable`, `Modal`)
- `layout/` - shell (`Shell`, `Header`, `Footer`)
- `forms/` - shared fields (`TextField`, `SelectField`)
- `shared/` - cross-feature widgets reused by 2+ unrelated routes (NOT single-feature screens, which colocate with their route)

**Ban** domain-named screen files at root (e.g. a single-resource list module sitting next to `Button.tsx`). Domain code belongs under the route or a domain folder. The `shared/` area is only for genuinely cross-feature widgets - if a component serves one feature, colocate it with that route.

### Monorepo test

Multiple deployable apps -> `apps/*` + shared `packages/*` when shapes are reused. Match **siblings** in the same app before inventing a new layout.

### Serializers / server lib

When DTO shapes are identical across apps -> shared package. Otherwise per-app `lib/serializers/` (or equivalent). Avoid redundant nested folder names under `lib/` when the app package already implies context (`lib/queries/`, `lib/cached/` - not `lib/storefront/storefront/`).

---

## Universal Root Layout (Every Project)

```
project-root/
├── .env.example           # Environment template (NEVER commit .env)
├── .gitignore
├── README.md              # Domain rules, flows, limits (see documentation.md)
├── LICENSE                # If open-source
├── rules/                 # This rulebook (copy to every project)
├── docs/                  # Setup, onboarding, architecture, ADRs, API docs
├── scripts/               # Build, deploy, seed, migration scripts
├── tests/                 # Integration / E2E tests (unit tests colocated)
└── src/                   # All application source code
```

---

## Web Application (React / Next.js / Vue / Svelte / Angular)

Example structure - adapt folder names and conventions to your framework (e.g. Next.js uses `app/` with file-based routing, Vue/Nuxt uses `pages/`, Angular uses `src/app/`):

```
src/
├── app/                   # Pages / routes / views (framework convention)
│   ├── (public)/          # Public pages group (unauthenticated routes)
│   ├── (main)/            # Protected pages group
│   ├── layout.*           # Root layout (shell, providers, metadata)
│   └── not-found.*        # 404 page
│
├── components/            # Shared UI components
│   ├── ui/                # Primitives: Button, Input, Modal, Card, Badge, Tooltip
│   ├── layout/            # Shell: Header, Sidebar, Footer, Navigation
│   └── shared/            # Cross-feature widgets (not domain list screens - those colocate with routes)
│
├── lib/                   # Core business logic (NO UI code)
│   ├── auth.ts            # Auth configuration, session helpers
│   ├── api.ts             # API client / fetch wrapper
│   ├── permissions.ts     # Permission definitions and check utilities
│   ├── constants.ts       # App-wide constants
│   ├── utils.ts           # Pure utility functions (formatDate, slugify, etc.)
│   └── validators.ts      # Shared validation schemas (using your schema library of choice)
│
├── hooks/                 # Custom hooks (React) or composables (Vue)
│   ├── useAuth.ts         # Authentication state hook
│   ├── usePermissions.ts  # Permission check hook
│   └── useDebounce.ts     # Utility hooks
│
├── services/              # External service integrations
│   ├── socket.ts          # WebSocket client (if applicable)
│   ├── storage.ts         # File upload / cloud storage client
│   └── tracking.ts        # Optional usage/telemetry client (omit if unused)
│
├── store/                 # Global state (using your state management library)
│   ├── slices/            # State slices / modules
│   └── index.ts           # Store configuration
│
├── types/                 # TypeScript types / interfaces (or language equivalent)
│   ├── models.ts          # Database model types
│   ├── api.ts             # API request/response types
│   └── index.ts           # Re-exports
│
├── styles/                # Global styles, CSS variables, theme
│   ├── globals.css        # Reset, CSS variables, base styles
│   ├── theme.ts           # Theme constants (if CSS-in-JS)
│   └── fonts/             # Custom font files
│
└── assets/                # Static assets (images, icons, animations)
    ├── icons/
    └── images/
```

