## SPA (Vite / CRA / Vue CLI + client router)

When the frontend is a **separate static SPA** (not Next.js/Nuxt file-based routing):

```
src/
├── main.tsx               # Entry, providers
├── App.tsx
├── router.tsx             # React Router (or equivalent)
├── auth/                  # Session, login, role guards
├── layouts/               # Shell layouts (nav, header, outlet)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                # Primitives not yet in shared package
│   ├── layout/            # Optional app-local layout pieces
│   └── forms/             # Shared form fields
├── hooks/                 # Cross-route hooks only
├── lib/                   # Client helpers (if not in shared api-client)
└── routes/                # URL-mirror - one folder per route segment
    ├── dashboard/
    │   ├── DashboardPage.tsx
    │   ├── components/    # Route-local UI only
    │   └── hooks/
    └── settings/
```

**Rules:** Same placement tests as other web apps (URL mirror, colocation, shared root limited to `ui/`, `layout/`, `forms/`). Data fetching via shared cache layer (`frontend.md`). API base URL from env at build time - never vendor secrets in the bundle.

**Monorepo:** SPA may live at `apps/web`, `website/`, or `packages/web/` - document the chosen name in `docs/architecture.md`.

