## API / Backend (Express / Fastify / Django / Rails / Spring / Laravel)

```
src/
├── config/                # App configuration
│   ├── database.ts        # DB connection, pool settings
│   ├── auth.ts            # JWT secret, bcrypt rounds, session config
│   ├── cors.ts            # Allowed origins, methods, headers
│   ├── rateLimit.ts       # Rate limit rules per endpoint category
│   └── environment.ts     # Environment variable validation and export
│
├── routes/                # Route definitions (thin - delegate to controllers)
│   ├── auth.routes.ts     # /api/auth/*
│   ├── users.routes.ts    # /api/users/*
│   ├── resources.routes.ts # /api/resources/*
│   └── index.ts           # Route aggregator
│
├── controllers/           # Request handlers (parse input -> call service -> return response)
│   ├── auth.controller.ts
│   ├── users.controller.ts
│   └── resources.controller.ts
│
├── services/              # Business logic (NO request/response objects here)
│   ├── auth.service.ts
│   ├── users.service.ts
│   └── resources.service.ts
│
├── models/                # Database models / entities / schemas
│   ├── User.ts
│   ├── Resource.ts
│   └── index.ts           # Re-exports all models
│
├── middleware/             # Express/framework middleware
│   ├── authenticate.ts    # Session verification middleware
│   ├── authorize.ts       # Permission check middleware
│   ├── validate.ts        # Request body validation middleware
│   ├── rateLimiter.ts     # Rate limiting middleware
│   └── errorHandler.ts    # Global error handler (catches all unhandled errors)
│
├── lib/                   # Shared utilities (same concept as frontend lib/)
│   ├── permissions.ts     # Permission definitions and check functions
│   ├── pagination.ts      # Pagination utility
│   ├── databaseErrors.ts  # Database error -> HTTP response mapper
│   ├── validators.ts      # Validation schemas
│   └── utils.ts           # Pure helper functions
│
├── types/                 # Shared types/interfaces
│
├── jobs/                  # Background jobs / cron tasks
│   ├── cleanExpiredRecords.ts
│   └── runScheduledJobs.ts
│
└── seeds/                 # Database seed data for development
    ├── users.seed.ts
    └── index.ts
```

**Framework Exceptions:**
- **Next.js / SvelteKit / Nuxt**: Use file-based routing in `app/` or `pages/` - no separate `routes/` and `controllers/` folders. Business logic still lives in `lib/` or `services/`.
- **Django**: Follow `apps/` convention but keep the same logical grouping inside each app.
- **Rails**: Follow `app/controllers`, `app/models`, `app/services` convention.
- **Laravel**: Follow `app/Http/Controllers`, `app/Models`, `app/Services` convention.

